Hello,

I did something pretty similar: https://github.com/Sysnove/letsencrypt-client/blob/master/files/letsencrypt-auto-renew.sh

@tasn one of the things you need to know is that if acme-tiny fails for any reason to generate the certificate, it will still echo an empty string on the output that will erase your previous cert. Be careful with that if you put your wrapper in a cron.

> So what's actually happening here? I'd like to document this in the README.

What's happening is that you're trying to install soundscrape via python3 which somehow has become the default on @mobiuscoffee system. Soundscrape is supposed to be installed under python2. So for 15.04 system you need to run `pip2 install soundscrape` to force the install under python2.

@Miserlou I can replicate this exact error by using `pip3 install soundscrape` which is the pip for python3. This is a problem of course since soundscrape is python2.

@mobiuscoffee your python install has defaulted to python3, and so when you run `pip` its actually running `pip3` you can verify this by going to Terminal and running `which pip` and you should see the result of `/usr/local/bin/pip` if you run `cat /usr/local/bin/pip` the first line of result will most likely be #!/usr/bin/python3. To fix see [my above comment.](https://github.com/Miserlou/SoundScrape/issues/5#issuecomment-125050403)

@gupta82anish moving to contentscript only involved updating my manifest.json, previously I was using it in background script but now i mention it contentscript section of the manifest.json.
Once I have created the zipped file from background scrip i convert it to string below is the code
`reader = new FileReader();
                        reader.readAsDataURL(content);
                        reader.onloadend = function() {
                                var base64data = reader.result;
                                chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tab_id, {method:'removeLoader', content:base64data, name:`${product_id}-${FolderIntials} Images.zip`});
                        }`
On contentscript side in the message listener i do the following:

`if(message.method === 'removeLoader'){
            message.content = message.content.slice(28);
            var blob = b64toBlob(message.content,'application/zip');
            // see FileSaver.js
                	saveAs(blob, message.name);

            removeLoader();

		}`

b64toBlob is a custom function and it downloads the zipped file.
In order to install from bower I use below command since only version 1.3.3 is working I have not tried the solution yet that @onaralili  provided 

`bower install file-saver#1.3.3`

Hope this helps

How do you generate the `__init__`? Do you generate source code that you them compile, or do you have a generic `__init__` that looks for the data in a special place on the class (e.g. `C.__data_class_extras__`)?

If the former, maybe
```python
def __init__(self, x=None):
    if x is None:
        self.x = []
    else:
        self.x = x
```
You'd have to special-case at list list, dict and set. I'd like to avoid actually importing `copy`, it's an annoying extra import.

I guess this document is an [API Declaration](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-spec/blob/master/versions/1.2.md#52-api-declaration) in swagger 1.2, so I cooked a minimal [Resource Listing](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-spec/blob/master/versions/1.2.md#51-resource-listing) as below, and place this document in right folder to verify your issue

```json
{
    "swaggerVersion":"1.2",
    "apis":[
    {"path":"/v2/isps"}
    ],
    "apiVersion":"2.0",
    "info":{
        "title":"",
        "description":""
    }
}
```

In swagger 1.2, the detailed authorization info should be declared in 'Resource Listing', and only scopes(for oauth2) in 'API Declaration'.

In your cases, the 'Authorizations' should be replaced to your 'Resource Listing' file. In this API declaration part, it should only have these stuffs:
```
{
  "authorizations":{
     "apiKey":[]
  }
}
```

