      // Adjust the display based on the window size
      if (window.innerHeight < 80 || window.innerWidth < 80) {
        // Blank if window is too small
        document.body.style.display = 'none';
      };
      if (window.innerWidth < 200 || window.innerHeight < 150) {
        document.getElementById('back-link').style.display = 'none';
        document.getElementById('help-link').style.display = 'none';
      };
      if (window.innerWidth < 200) {
        document.getElementById('sorry').style.fontSize = '16px';
      };
      if (window.innerWidth < 150) {
        document.getElementById('promise').style.display = 'none';
      };
      if (window.innerHeight < 150) {
        document.getElementById('sorry').style.margin = '4px 0 0 0';
        document.getElementById('sorry').style.fontSize = '14px';
        document.getElementById('promise').style.display = 'none';
      };
    </script>
  </body>
</html>```

I don't know whether the warnings point to an actual problem, but I managed to get rid of the first set of five warnings (`patterns.Mockup Base: This mockup pattern without a name attribute will not be registered!`) by doing the following.  I wish I could point to a commit, but I can't figure out which branch/tag (of mockup, I assume) p.a.widgets 1.8.0 is built from.

The following all extend `LinkType`:  `InternalLink`, `UploadLink`, `ImageLink`, `EmailLink`, `AnchorLink`.

So, first, I added a `name` attribute to each of them.  But that's not enough, because after they have names, then it complains that they don't have triggers.  So I made the properties object that is passed to `.extend` get some default values from the parent (`LinkType`):

    var ImageLink = InternalLink.extend(_.defaults({
      name: "ImageLink",

      toUrl: function() {
        var value = this.value();
        return this.tinypattern.generateImageUrl(value, this.linkModal.$scale.val());
      }
    }, LinkType));

The two diffs here are the `name:`, and the `_.defaults(......, LinkType)`.

I have no idea whether this will break anything else, but I'd be happy to commit this change if it's ok and someone could point me to the right branch/whatever.

This does not fix the `patterns.Mockup Base: The mockup pattern 'plone-widgets' does not have a trigger attribute, it will not be registered.` warning.

