Hi enira, 

I've recently had to deal with a similar problem (though I'm using vSphere SDK for Perl) and I found the following list very useful: http://files.hypervisor.fr/vcEvents.html. To get VM created events, you'll probably have to look for all these: `"VmCreatedEvent", "VmClonedEvent", "VmDeployedEvent", "VmRegisteredEvent"`. Here's an example for Perl:
```perl
my $vmEventsCollector = Vim::get_view( mo_ref => $eventMgr->CreateCollectorForEvents( filter => EventFilterSpec->new( 
	eventTypeId => [ "VmCreatedEvent", "VmClonedEvent", "VmDeployedEvent", "VmRegisteredEvent" ],
	entity => EventFilterSpecByEntity->new( entity => $vm, recursion => EventFilterSpecRecursionOption->new( "self" ) ) 
)) );
my $eventsColl = $vmEventsCollector->ReadNextEvents( maxCount => 1 );
foreach my $event ( @$eventsColl ) {
	print( "Event for ". $vm->name . ":\t" . $event->createdTime . "\t" . $event->fullFormattedMessage . "\t" . $event->userName . "\n" );
}
```
Hope this helps.

