@joshgav, out of curiosity, what are you using the command for that makes performance/short parameter version desirable? 

To give you some context, the az cli is less monolithic and more component based than the previous xplat cli. Just having the CLI installed does not guarantee that you have the specific commands (or version of the commands) that you are interested in installed. We do intent to have a core set of packages be included in the basic install, but you can add/remove from the set at any point. In other words, knowing that only the base cli is available and can be loaded may not be accomplishing what you want.

Oh, and the reason that we haven't enabled -v (even though it is pretty much a standard flag) is that we are trying to avoid "squatting on" short parameter names from other commands. It is not a hard & fast rule (we did decide to use -h for help), so we are more than open to feedback on this.

