I'm not sure this is the right fix. The second order information is being computed but never used. This is an O(N * F * F) operation where F is the number of features (which is around 1K).

```
// Compute validation-set stats.
if (lr_interface->num_validation_examples() > 0) {
         // Recycle lvalues from stats to use as out parameters here, now that we're
        // otherwise done reading from stats.
        lr_interface->compute_validation_second_order_statistics(
             stats.solution, stats.hessian, stats.gradient, stats.func_value);
             state["validation_loss"] =  stats.func_value;
}
```

This is an extremely expensive operation and I'm not sure why we are doing it at the end of training. The right fix should be to replace that function with

```
 lr_interface->compute_validation_first_order_statistics
```

If that function doesn't exist, we should add it since the code that follows doesn't actually need to compute the Hessian.

