This worked to get me a normal object returned, rather than a JSON blob.  I created my own field type as such:

    from graphene.types.scalars import Scalar
    
    class ObjectField(Scalar):
    
        @staticmethod
        def serialize(dt):
            return dt
    
        @staticmethod
        def parse_literal(node):
            return node.value
    
        @staticmethod
        def parse_value(value):
            return value

Then I just use this as my type for the ``bug_suggestions`` field like so:

    bug_suggestions = ObjectField()

I understand why this may be considered by some to be "against GraphQL" because you can't specifically specify which parts of ``bug_suggestions`` get returned.  In my case, I don't care.  I want to return the whole thing and not have to specify it in my query.  Perhaps this will help someone sometime.  :)

